谢谢你帮我们整理我妈妈的东西
Thanks for helping us sort through all my mom's stuff.

62
00:02:32,260 --> 00:02:33,900
不用谢
Of course.

63
00:02:33,910 --> 00:02:35,170
我知道 去翻看
I know what it's like

64
00:02:35,170 --> 00:02:37,840
所爱之人的遗物 是什么样的感受
having to go through a loved one's possessions.

65
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:40,480
我的叔叔崇拜的是奎师那
My uncle was a worshipper of Krishna.

66
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:43,080
但他去世以后 你知道我们发现什么了吗?
But after he died, you know what we found?

67
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:46,280
一个湿婆的塑像
A statue of Shiva.

68
00:02:48,620 --> 00:02:50,290
虽然不是什么血雨腥风的帮派对头
It may not be Crips and Bloods, okay?

69
00:02:50,290 --> 00:02:52,550
但在印度 这也算是个事
But in India, it's a thing.

70
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,880
呃 你在就好
Well, it'll be good that you're there.

71
00:02:55,890 --> 00:02:57,160
Howard难以决定
Howard's been having trouble deciding

72
00:02:57,160 --> 00:02:59,090
什么要留下来什么要丢掉
what to keep and what to let go.

73
00:02:59,090 --> 00:03:00,550
啊 这是很难
Well, it's hard.

74
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:03,790
妈妈的很多东西都会勾起一些快乐的回忆
A lot of Ma's stuff brings back fond memories.

75
00:03:03,790 --> 00:03:05,220
所以你才不愿意丢掉
Is that why you couldn't get rid of

76
00:03:05,220 --> 00:03:08,030
她那个装满番茄酱的抽屉吗?
her drawer full of ketchup packets?

77
00:03:08,030 --> 00:03:11,190
是啊 这让我记起来 我们在外面吃饭的时候 她对我说
Yes. It reminds me of us eating out and her saying,

78
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:14,230
"快 没人看着 多拿点番茄酱放你口袋里"
"Quick, nobody's looking, fill your pockets with ketchup"

79
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:23,520
Leonard啊?
Leonard?

80
00:03:23,530 --> 00:03:26,630
你有没有注意过
Have you ever noticed that

81
00:03:26,630 --> 00:03:30,360
有线电视的账单上只有我的名字?
only my name is on the cable bill?

82
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:32,860
是的
Yeah.

83
00:03:32,870 --> 00:03:35,570
好的 好的
Good, good.

84
00:03:35,570 --> 00:03:37,470
电费单上只有你的名字
And your name is on the electric bill

85
00:03:37,470 --> 00:03:39,370
而没有我的 
and mine isn't.

86
00:03:39,370 --> 00:03:40,670
而且我对这件事没什么意见
And I'm okay with that.

87
00:03:40,670 --> 00:03:43,140
其实 电费单上写的是你的名字
Actually, your name is on the electric bill.

88
00:03:43,150 --> 00:03:45,080
哦 对哦
Oh, right.

89
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:49,980
真是个灾难
This is a disaster.

90
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:53,410
我完全不知道你在讲什么 我还同意你的说法
I don't even know what you're talking about and I agree.

91
00:03:53,410 --> 00:03:57,120
好吧 有件事我要告诉你
Okay, I have to tell you something,

92
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:59,130
但你会不高兴的
but you're not going to like it.

93
00:03:59,130 --> 00:04:00,530
怎么了?
What's going on?

94
00:04:00,530 --> 00:04:02,990
科学美国人上发表了一篇
An article was just published

95
00:04:02,990 --> 00:04:06,000
关于我们理论的文章
in Scientific American about our theory.

96
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,600
他们很讨厌它吗?
Did they hate it?

97
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,670
不 不 他们爱死它了
No. No, they loved it.

98
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:12,270
他们 呃 说了一大堆好话
They, uh, couldn't say enough nice things about it.

99
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:14,840
那有什么问题吗?
So what's the problem?

100
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:19,310
你知道我们的省钱一族...
You know how the Penny Saver only has my name...

101
00:04:19,320 --> 00:04:20,580
Sheldon啊!
Sheldon!

102
00:04:20,580 --> 00:04:23,250
那篇文章里他们没有提到你
They didn't mention you in the article.

103
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:24,650
只提到了我
Only me.

104
00:04:24,650 --> 00:04:26,460
真的?
Really?

105
00:04:26,460 --> 00:04:27,580
是啊
I know.

106
00:04:27,590 --> 00:04:29,790
这不公平
It's not fair.

107
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:34,700
放下你的怒火 兄弟
Let the anger go, buddy.

108
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:36,130
你...
You just...

109
00:04:36,140 --> 00:04:38,840
放松所有的肌肉
you relax all your muscles.

110
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:41,570
除了你的耻尾肌和肛管括约肌
Except for your pubococcygeus and anal sphincter.

111
00:04:41,580 --> 00:04:44,140
那两个要收紧了
Let's keep those tight.

112
00:04:44,140 --> 00:04:47,410
呃 不... 你不需要这样的
Uh, that... that's not necessary.

113
00:04:47,410 --> 00:04:50,010
其实需要... 他们是帮你憋尿憋屎用的
It is... they're what hold back the urine and the feces.

114
00:04:50,010 --> 00:04:52,950
听着 也许... 也许你不该读
Look, maybe... maybe you shouldn't read it.

115
00:04:52,950 --> 00:04:54,880
你只会感觉更糟糕
It'll only make you feel worse.

116
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:57,420
"Cooper和他的团队"?
"Cooper and his team"?

117
00:04:57,420 --> 00:04:59,890
你要知道这件事和我完全没关系
You should know I had nothing to do with that.

118
00:04:59,890 --> 00:05:01,960
呃...
Uh...

119
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:04,630
至少他们在讨论这个理论
at least they're talking about the theory.

120
00:05:04,630 --> 00:05:06,860
我是说 这个最重要
I mean, that's what's important.

121
00:05:06,860 --> 00:05:09,330
你说的对
You know, you're right.

122
00:05:09,330 --> 00:05:12,400
是啊 就像斯坦·李和史蒂夫·迪特科
Yeah. You know, it's like when Stan Lee and Steve Ditko

123
00:05:12,410 --> 00:05:14,170
一起创作了蜘蛛侠
created Spider-Man.

124
00:05:14,180 --> 00:05:16,010
功劳全被斯坦·李占了
Stan Lee may get all the credit,

125
00:05:16,010 --> 00:05:18,980
但是史蒂夫·迪特科知道他也一样重要
but Steve Ditko knows he was just as important.

126
00:05:18,990 --> 00:05:21,880
虽然斯坦·李可以在所有的漫威电影里出镜
Even though Stan Lee gets to be in all the Marvel movies.

127
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:23,520
而且... 而且他还很有钱
And... and he's far richer.

128
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:25,710
而且他是个家喻户晓的人了 对吧?
And he's a household name, you know?

129
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:28,020
但是 你说迪斯科
Whereas, you know, you say Ditko,

130
00:05:28,020 --> 00:05:30,690
听上去感觉是个公司的名字
and that sounds like a company that makes Dits.

131
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:34,990
你这是帮倒忙
That's not helping.

132
00:05:36,490 --> 00:05:38,360
好吧 我能再多举几个例子的
Well, I'd give more examples,

133
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:41,830
但是像你这样被遗落的人 实在太难想起来还有谁了
but, well, everyone in your position's so forgettable.

134
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:46,600
Stuart 我们来了
Stuart, we're here.

135
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:49,470
你让他继续住在你妈妈的屋子真好
It's nice of you to let him keep staying at your mom's house.

136
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:52,070
是啊 我本来想把他丢到路边去的
Yeah, well, I tried putting him out on the curb,

137
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:53,940
但是没有人愿意收留他
but nobody took him.

138
00:05:54,870 --> 00:05:56,540
嘿
Hey.

139
00:05:56,550 --> 00:05:58,540
跟你说一下 这里停电了
Just so you know, the power's out.

140
00:05:58,550 --> 00:05:59,740
怎么了?
What happened?

141
00:05:59,740 --> 00:06:02,050
我打电话问了 他们说一个变压器爆炸了
I called, they said a transformer blew.

142
00:06:02,050 --> 00:06:03,120
整个街区都停电了
It's the whole block.

143
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:04,350
应该明天就修好了
Should be fixed by tomorrow.

144
00:06:04,350 --> 00:06:06,180
等等 什么时候停电的?
Wait, when did it go out?

145
00:06:06,180 --> 00:06:07,650
半夜的时候
In the middle of the night.

146
00:06:07,650 --> 00:06:10,360
哦 天啊
Oh, my God.

147
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:12,730
Howie 怎么了?
Howie, what's wrong?

148
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:17,230
全都解冻了
It's all defrosting.

149
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,900
没事的 只是食物而已
It's okay. It's just food.

150
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:21,680
这不只是食物
It's not just food.

151
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:24,740
这是我妈做的唯一剩下的食物
This is the last food my mother ever made.

152
00:06:25,780 --> 00:06:27,080
这是她仅剩的牛胸肉
This is her last brisket.

153
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:28,750
这是她仅剩的烘肉卷
This is her last meatloaf.

154
00:06:28,750 --> 00:06:30,210
这是她仅剩的...
This is her last...

155
00:06:31,860 --> 00:06:34,820
我看不出这是什么 但是...
I have no idea what this is, but...

156
00:06:34,820 --> 00:06:37,690
这是仅剩的了
it's the last one.

157
00:06:37,690 --> 00:06:39,290
一切还好吗?
Everything okay?

158
00:06:39,290 --> 00:06:40,490
不好
No.

159
00:06:40,490 --> 00:06:43,490
老妈做的所有食物都要变质了
All Ma's food is gonna be ruined.

160
00:06:43,490 --> 00:06:45,900
我们为什么不拿回家 放进咱们的冰箱里?
Well, why don't we take it home and put it in our freezer?

161
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:47,530
你不会想这么做的
You don't want to do that.

162
00:06:47,530 --> 00:06:49,500
再冰冻不仅会使它脱水
Refreezing not only removes moisture,

163
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:51,800
更会在肉纤维表面形成冰晶
but it creates ice crystals in the fibers of the meat

164
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:54,700
进而影响口感和质地
that can compromise its taste and texture.

165
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,440
怎么了? 我看到说教的机会
What? I saw a teachable moment.

166
00:06:57,440 --> 00:06:59,870
就显摆了些烹饪学问
I dropped some culinary science.

167
00:07:01,910 --> 00:07:03,740
我们该怎么办呢?
What should we do?

168
00:07:03,740 --> 00:07:06,080
我来告诉你该怎么办
I'll tell you exactly what we're gonna do.

169
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:07,920
把它吃了
We're gonna eat it.

170
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:09,820
这里差不不多有二十磅的食物
There's, like, 20 pounds of food in there.

171
00:07:09,820 --> 00:07:10,920
你只说过
All you said

172
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,490
我要处理掉它们
was I had to get rid of things.

173
00:07:12,490 --> 00:07:15,490
又没说不能让它们先通过我的肠道
You didn't say they couldn't pass through my colon first.

174
00:07:15,490 --> 00:07:18,760
哎Howie...
Howie...

175
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:20,400
好吧
Okay.

176
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:22,870
那这样吧?
Then how about this?

177
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:25,040
我们请大家过来吃晚饭
Let's invite everyone over to dinner.

178
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:29,050
就当是老妈做的最后一顿饭
It'll be like Ma's feeding us one last time.

179
00:07:29,050 --> 00:07:31,950
我喜欢这主意
I love that.

180
